This paper deals with algorithms for the Maximal Clique Listing problem, which is a problem in graph theory. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories related to algorithms and graph theory. Specifically, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are all possible sub-categories that could be relevant to this paper. Among these, cs.DS and cs.DM are the most likely, as they are directly related to the design and analysis of algorithms for discrete structures such as graphs.
